-- RELEVANT FILE STRUCTURE -- 

 /var/www/gustavbjorelius_dev/nginx-conf/ 
  This is ?

 /etc/nginx/nginx.conf 
  Think: BRAIN
  This is the top level config over all domains. Rarely touch this. Log formats \
   gzip, connection limits. 
  Simpler as Cloudflared Tunnel is used. No SSL Certs. Though, important, it must \
   listen to port 80. This happens in the server block
  Configure it to only accept trafic from Cloudflare, so bypassing Cloudflare. 

 /etc/nginx/sites-available
  Think: LIBRARY

 /etc/nginx/sites-enabled
  Symlinks made from ln /etc/nginx/sites-available /etc/nginx/sites-enabled

 /etc/php/8.x/fpm/pool.d/www.conf
  Adjust user perms and mem limits 
  Q: what and why are these?

 /etc/php/8.x/fpm/php.ini
  PHP Configuration 

 /run/php/php8.x-fpm.sock
  Path nginx will 'talk' to
  Since Nginx doesn't have naitive comms w php, it must send files to PHP-FPM
  Replace x with the correct version

 /var/log/nginx/access.log
  You see every single visitor and their IP 
  tail -f /path/to/log | grep -E "error" 
  grep -E "error|keyWords" /path/to/log
  less /path/to/log
   vi like movements and search 

